# Keep local-only ENV files OUT of the prod image. .env.local holds the local
# single-origin-gateway values (NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_HOST=/auth,
# DJANGO_API_URL=localhost) which `next build` would otherwise bake into the
# production bundle — breaking the central-auth redirect (it pointed at /auth on
# the tenant domain instead of auth.startsimpli.com).
#
# node_modules is EXCLUDED: the @startsimpli/* are published now, so the image is
# built reproducibly from the lockfile (Dockerfile step `pnpm install
# --frozen-lockfile`). Copying the local node_modules in is fragile — if it's
# linked to the monorepo's shared pnpm store (e.g. after a workspace `pnpm add`),
# the symlinks dangle in the image and `next build` fails to resolve its own bin.
node_modules
.env.local
.env*.local
.git
